Hear directly from WHO’s regional director in Africa, the Minister of Health of South Africa, and more, about the latest status of the novel coronavirus across the continent, and their answers to journalists’ most pressing questions. Supported by the World Economic Forum. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Health, Dr Zweli Mkhize is briefing World Economic Forum on COVID-19. This is a joint briefing between the World Health Organization and the World Economic Forum. Mkhize: COVID-19 patterns are changing Mkhize and the WHO’s regional director in Africa, Matshidiso Moeti will field questions on the coronavirus in the continent. Africa has over 3 million confirmed cases od COVID-19, with about 228,000 deaths. Around 970,000 people have recovered.